          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "92-U-235",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.95
              },
              "free_text": [
                " 28.5 g and 54.1 g of 95 percent",
                "U235 (metal) disks."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "REC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A proton recoil counter has been used to",
                "determine the neutron spectrum in the energy range",
                "3.3-17 MeV. The data were fitted with the equation",
                "N(En)=5.5 x 10**5 P exp(-En/1.3), where En is neutron",
                "energy in MeV and P is \"Water Boiler\" reactor power",
                "level in kilowatts (proportional to source strength).",
                "The spectrum produced by the fission in the disks",
                "alone was obtained by subtracting the values given by",
                "the above-mentioned equation from the values obtained",
                "for the beam from the multiple disk source."
              ]
            }
          ],
